Love this movie so much! I love that it's a true story. I saw it in the theater a number of times and we've given it as a gift as well. Everyone we know that's seen it was deeply impacted. We also bought it with the documentary done four years before that interviews the actual people involved in the true story. So interesting! They are a great pair of DVD's to gift to any family.

The story of 5 missionary families in Equador in the 1950s. The men were murdered by fearful tribe members because of a lie one of the tribal members perpetrated. The story is told from the perspective of one of the missionarys sons who is now an adult. Beautiful picture of love, forgiveness, and the transforming power of Christ.
